reviews.review_text: Great Versions Of Everything Every version of every song played at this show was phenomenal.  I will admit, the recording has a few minor glitches but they don't take away from the overall greatness of this show as a whole.  You will not regret downloading this one.  Very beautiful.

Cool Bay Area Evening - Crisp Guitarwork I attended this show. I don't remember how good it sounded until listening to shn. Very good sound quality.

It was cold that evening, and I remember the really nice scarlet fire. All songs are played quite well, and the guitar work from Jerry, Bob, and Phil comes accross as being crisp and clean.

A good copy for the collection for the most part. After drumz, every song has some interference. Also, Lucy in the Sky is cut off near the end. 
I give it four stars more for the performance, although the sound quality on the most part is superior.

08.25.93 An excellent night of music. The energy was there from the start and the Boyz brought a really tight, sharp first set. The "So Many Roads" cooked. With Jerry really getting into the strong lyrical end and punching his fist to the air. That just feed a ROCKIN' "Promised Land." The Boyz just jammed it out and out. Strong finish to a really great first set. Second set, WOW! The whole second set is great. The only bad thing I remember is the sound during sections of the second set, especially during "Attics." It seems like the sound was trying to be to loud and came out distorted at times. But, even then great second set, and a good LOOSE "Lucy in the Sky" with Phil giving the "let's round up it" signal by swirling his arm above and around his head. Not the tightest version, but a great closer to a really great show.

Forgotten gem from 1993 Great gift for my 20th show. The So Many Roads is intense, the Scarlet>Fire wonderfully engaging and the rock and roll is rocking. Great sound quality, everyone in the band seems to be happy to be playing. Get it.

good stuff If you listen to this show and start getting nervous while listening to touch of grey, fear not! The big boy's vocals and playing on that tune are sloppy but nothing from there on is bad. Nice first set with yet another Amazing so many roads.(seems like we all keep saying that). second set is money with the big 4 before drums. Some tech troubles after space, but nothing that should deter you from this one.

Shoreline 1993 First night of the 3 day run.  This is a very nice show and the quality is great.  The second set has an above average setlist and the boys were playing well.   I recommend all 3 Shoreline shows from this run. Enjoy!
good roads wind the ol juke box up one more time... good mix.

So Many Roads... but only one bus! This was show #101 for me. 
If there is a better So Many Roads ever I'd like to know. 
People rave about Shoreline 9/18/94 with the extended outro jam and second go ' round of Jerry's BIG Diva ending but this one is picture perfect.  Yes Salt Lake 95 is special but this is THE ONE!!! Even nails all of the lyrics!!!
 Nice Scarlet >Fire and save the static a pretty Attics as well.

a better so many roads Hey DJJazz, check out the So Many Roads from 6/8/92 at the Richfield Coliseum. this is when Jerry started doing the big EASE MY SOUL outro part, you can hear the crowd go nuts on the soundboard version, but a good audience version makes the hair on my arms stand up every time, plus i was second row , front and center.

Peggy-O One of my favorite Dead songs.
Not the most popular but great nonetheless.
